verses.roman:
āge sampradāye nṛtya kare haridāsa
madhye nāce ācārya-gosāñi parama ullāsa

synonyms: āge—in front; sampradāye—in the party; nṛtya—dancing; kare—does; haridāsa—Ṭhākura Haridāsa; madhye—in the middle; nāce—dances; ācārya-gosāñi—Śrī Advaita Ācārya; parama—very; ullāsa—happy.
translation: In the front party danced Ṭhākura Haridāsa, and in the middle party danced Advaita Ācārya with great jubilition.
